# How to Use Toast Notifications with Sonner (`sonner.tsx`)

## Context

We use the [Sonner](https://sonner.emilkowal.ski/) library for toast notifications in our application.  
The component wrapper is defined in `src/components/ui/sonner.tsx` and is named `Toaster`.  
It is a Client Component and automatically adapts to the current theme using `next-themes`.

## Usage

- Import and render the `Toaster` component **once** at the root of your app (e.g., in `layout.tsx` or `_app.tsx`).
- Use the Sonner API (`import { toast } from "sonner"`) to trigger notifications anywhere in your client-side code.

## Example

```tsx
// In your layout or root component
import { Toaster } from "@/components/ui/sonner";

export function RootLayout({ children }: { children: React.ReactNode }) {
  return (
    <>
      <Toaster />
      {children}
    </>
  );
}
```

```tsx
// In any client component
"use client";
import { toast } from "sonner";

export function MyButton() {
  return (
    <button
      onClick={() => toast.success("Operation successful!")}
    >
      Show Toast
    </button>
  );
}